Chaospill #342
metadata.description:
A chaotic algorithm spilling out of control.

Click to randomize with the same settings.

By Frank Force @KilledByAPixel
Made with Vanilla JavaScript

Controls
1 = Save a 2048x2048 png (or right click save)
2 = Toggle 8192x8192 HD (may not work in some browsers)
3 = Toggle noise (disable for clearer image)
4 = Auto randomize every 30 seconds

metadata.name: Chaosplot #131
metadata.description:
Continued exploration of the algorithm from "Chaospill" with a symmetric two tone style that is plotter friendly. The result can be rotated to whatever orientation works best for your display purposes. The code is presented unminified with comments and will be open sourced soon.

Live Mode Controls

Click to regenerate with a different starting seed.
1 - Save a SVG, the result is sized for 11"x17" prints with each color on a separate layer
2 - Save a PNG of the output
3 - Switch paper size to 8.5"x11" letter or A1 for different size plots
4 - Toggle HD mode which increases resolution and disables noise for printing

Code and Outputs are Copyright (C) 2022 Frank Force - Artwork is released under CC BY-NC 4.0.

metadata.name: a fleeting moment #31
metadata.description:
Abstract expressionism always has been, and always will be, my first love. With this piece, the initial premise was "can I write a bit of code that will render images in the style that I actually paint in real life?" 

It took several full days of poking and prodding, and I departed from the original mission once I had what I was looking for, but in general, I think I succeeded. My wife was looking over my shoulder at one point, and thought I was looking at a scan of one of my actual paintings, which sounds like success to me. 

Created with love in p5.js

metadata.name: Canyon #127
metadata.description:
Canyon is a generative art project inspired by canyons and reinterpreted in 9 different styles (that each have their own specificities):
- Grand Canyon
- Radioactive
- Blue Grotto
- Black Crystals
- Magma
- Iceberg
- Imagination
- UV
- Sandstone

Accessories (Kayak, Rowing Boat, Barrels) are present on some variations (in this case, it is possible to generate a second variation without accessories by pressing "a").

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.
